<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
   <teiHeader>
      <fileDesc>
         <titleStmt>
            <title>Mary Behrend's Calendar Sheets</title>
            <author>Mary Behrend</author>
            <editor>Austin Murry</editor>
         </titleStmt>
         
         <publicationStmt>
            <p>Was never published by Mary Behrend</p>
         </publicationStmt>
         <sourceDesc>
            
           <msDesc>
              <msIdentifier><repository>Penn State Erie, The Behrend College Library</repository></msIdentifier>
              <physDesc>
                 <handDesc>
                    <handNote xml:id="calendarPub" medium="print">New Friendship Calendar Company printing the calendar sheets.</handNote>
                    <handNote xml:id="redPen" medium="red inkpen">Probably Mary Behrend writing in a red pen.
                    </handNote>
                    <handNote xml:id="blackPen" medium="black inkpen">Probably Mary Behrend writing in a black pen.
                       Usually this pen is clearer to read and the writing is larger. 
                    </handNote>
                 </handDesc>

              </physDesc>
             
           </msDesc>
           <!-- ebb: I'm not sure where we can put the original paragraph Austin wrote for the sourceDesc, 
              but I think there will be another part of teiHeader where we can describe the source overall. 
              Possibly we can find another entry for the physDesc, just digging around a little more.
              
              <p>Calendar sheets written and illustrated by Mary Behrend found in an old baby book,
               inside of an envelope.</p>
           
           -->
         </sourceDesc>
      </fileDesc>
   </teiHeader>
   <text>
      <body>
         <div1 type="calendarSheets">
            <fw type="header" place="top-centre" hand="#calendarPub">
               <lb/>Copyright 1908 by <lb/>Friendship Calendar Co. <lb/>New Britain, Conn.</fw>
            
            <div2 n="1">
               <fw>
                  <lb/><date when="1909-03-11">March 11, 1909 <lb/>Thursday</date>
               <!--ebb: I'm adding an @when attribute to hold a standardized form of the date, like this:
               yyyy-mm-dd. That's the xsd:date datatype, and it'll help later with processing this information maybe in a timeline or 
               do calculations like find out how much time passes in between each of her calendar sketches. 
               -->
               </fw>
               <figure>
                  <graphic
                     url="https://newtfire.org/courses/tutorials/TEI-images/mary-behrend-calendar-1909/IMG_2049.jpg"/>
                  <figDesc>Graphic of four women dressed in differrent colors, and one woman on the
                     left (dressed in red) and one on the right (dressed in green) are yelling at a
                     woman in the middle (dressed in blue)</figDesc>
               </figure>
               <ab>
                  <lb/>Everybody dressed in their best <lb/>For this is an <emph style="underline"
                     >Erie Tea</emph>
                  <lb/>They <emph style="underline">eat</emph> too much, <emph style="underline"
                     >talk</emph> too much- <lb/>You can bet they dont ???? in me.</ab>
            </div2>
            
            <div2 n="2">
               <head>
                  <lb/>March 12, 1909 <lb/>Friday</head>
               <figure>
                  <graphic
                     url="https://newtfire.org/courses/tutorials/TEI-images/mary-behrend-calendar-1909/IMG_2050.jpg"/>
                  <figDesc>Drawing of Molly Behrend walking in snowshoes, along the left hand side
                     of the page</figDesc>
               </figure>
               <ab>
                  <lb/>Molly on <lb/>snowshoes <lb/>that Mr. Weir <lb/>got. <lb/>Pretty picture
                  <lb/>is it not?!</ab>
            </div2>
            
            <div2 n="3">
               <head>
                  <lb/>March 17, 1909. <lb/>Wednesday <lb/>St. Patrick's Day</head>
               <figure>
                  <graphic
                     url="https://newtfire.org/courses/tutorials/TEI-images/mary-behrend-calendar-1909/IMG_2052.jpg"/>
                  <figDesc>Graphic of snakes and clovers below the date line</figDesc>
               </figure>
               <ab hand="#blackPen">
                  <lb/>St. Patricks was a useful saint <lb/>He fightened all the snakes away- <lb/>I
                  wish he'd try his art on <emph style="underline">smoke</emph>
                  <lb/>Around the Hammermill some day!</ab>
               <figure>
                  <graphic
                     url="https://newtfire.org/courses/tutorials/TEI-images/mary-behrend-calendar-1909/IMG_2052.jpg"/>
                  <figDesc>a clover in between the last two lines, between "smoke" and "some day"
                     and one near the bottom of the page next to a drawing of the Hammermll Paper
                     Company.</figDesc>
               </figure>
            </div2>
            
         </div1>
      </body>
   </text>
</TEI>
